message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Albania in the past 20 years is the 2019 earthquake. On November 26, 2019, a magnitude 6.4 earthquake struck the country, causing widespread destruction and claiming the lives of 51 people. Thousands of buildings were damaged or destroyed, leaving many people homeless. The earthquake prompted a massive national and international response, with rescue teams, volunteers, and aid pouring into the affected areas. It was a tragic event that had a profound impact on the country and its people.
